items.name: Bound Arms
items.description:
This Lora helps produce a girl with her arms bound behind her back, mainly with rope. Models are already alright with this, especially any bondage mixes, but this was made to help with consistency and test the effect of only using illustrations to train bondage. Plus, it helps if you don't want to use a bondage mix either. Generally hands are just obscured while using this, it definitely doesn't help them when they do show. Although I did tag what I saw, I didn't end up including enough "from behind" images in the training set for this to perform well for that.

Trigger Words:

bound arms, arms behind back

technically only "bound arms" is the trigger, but adding "arms behind back" seems to improve its performance.

Note: one issue I've found is a tendency to try and add a gag regardless of prompt, so add

gag, gagged

to the negative prompt to counteract that.

items.name: Ranger (Kancolle)
items.description:
An experimental character LoRA of Ranger from Kantai Collection.

Info

Training with 65 images, contain few image of costume variation
Followed the manual form [ [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free ],
You can access to this guide in Suggested Resources section.

Recommended set up

Sampler: Euler a, DPM family series
Sampling steps: 20 or 25+
CFG Scale: 7
CLIP Skip: 2
*Do not use [restore face] on anime character!*

LoRA Weighting: [0.95 - 0.85], (1 - 0.6)

Baking Step:
0. Drafting (512 x 512 res to find your desired sketch)
1. Hires fix (txt2img: 768 x 768, 768 x 512, 512 x 768, or above res)
2. inpaint (img2img: refine some unwanted effect, [Euler a] with 50+ step)
3. Upscaling (img2img: res*2 with [ControlNet Tile] & Ultimate SD upscale)

Upscaler for [Step 1 - 3]: [R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B, 4x-AnimeSharp, 4x-UltraSharp]
I always skip Step 0, 2 :P

Basic prompts

RangerKC, (blue and white)_two-tone dress, (blue skirt), short sleeves, blue necktie, white gloves, pantyhose, side braids

Special outfits

RangerSanma

RangerKC, RangerSanma, white jacket, long sleeves, blue denim skirt, black pantyhose, boots, black footwear

OPTIONAL:fishing rod, white fishing cooler

Rangerkimono (Ref to New Year costume)

RangerKC, Rangerkimono, light aqua kimono, big white fur collar covering neck

RangerOni

RangerKC, RangerOni, (tiger print)_pinafore dress, BREAK,(red sweater:1.3), BREAK, horn, black thighhighs

Drunk Ranger

closed eyes, blush, holding wine glass, drinking glass, alcohol, wine, drunk, drooling

Some additional tags that you may use for reference

-fang, 1.8L sake bottle

  • LORA weight for txt2img: 0.5-1 (for the examples i mostly used 0.8 and 1)

  • Denoise strength upscaling: 0.3 to 0.55

If you want to autocomplete the tags & trigger im using, I recommend using Booru style tag autocompletion for AUTOMATIC1111's Stable Diffusion web UI

items.name: Dragan High Contrast Style
items.description: Here is a Lora for the photographic Dragan effect. It's a very high contrast photographic style. This works great on close portraits of older people, as it accentuates wrinkles, but it works on all sorts of photos. Add the word 'Dragan' into your prompt with the lora. Adjust the strength of the effect by adjusting the number after the colon : <lora:dragan-06:0.1> to <lora:dragan-06:1>. As this photographic style is used mainly for closeups it is trained on mainly close ups, so you may need controlnet to get wider shots. Don't use restore faces or it will try to fix the style and remove wrinkles. Can be applied to other models to give more contract and definition. I hope you find this useful.

items.name: Honey 2D
items.description:
Cause water doesn't come this THICC!

You want thicc thighs, wide hips, gloooorious squishes all around? Your squishes to be mouth watering like a freshly opened tube of biscuits? So does this model!!

V2: Same great figure, now with better faces! It'll play really nice with face TI's and Loras! Enjoy!

As shown in the nurse pics above, a couple parenthesis can go a loooong way!

This model is meant to produce what I find to be the most screen-grabbing 2D I could possibly manage at the moment, so it'll take some time and lots of testing for me to update it.

NSFW promo images are in the gallery below.

There is no baked in VAE.
The VAE I use: Grapefruit VAE

As like my other models, my usual settings:

Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras
Sample Steps: 20-35
Upscaler: ESRGAN_4x
Deniose: 0.5
CFG: 5-9

By no means is this law, feel free to experiment and I'd love to see your results!!

For inpainting, you can use whatever res you'd like! There's no realism models present, so it won't get overly-detailed at 800+ res like my semi-realism models. You shouldn't need to change your prompt at all when inpainting faces to get a good result. This is always a goal of mine, as I prefer not to have to do any extra steps in my workflow if possible.

All images above were inpainted using the same prompt I used to make the image.

items.name: Wet Plate Collodion
items.description:
The wet plate collodion process is a photographic technique invented in the 19th Century, using graph plates covered in a chemical solution to produce images. The solution used is syrupy and viscous, resulting in a distinctive swirly distortion at the edges of the image. The silver nitrate in the developing solution creates a beautiful tonal range and a delicate crystalline grain.

This model was trained on real examples of wet plate collodion photographs to recreate the shades and textures of this vintage artform.
